    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/31.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am just in receipt of the following telegram protesting against allowing a
                    regiment of Mexican troops to pass over Texas soil from Eagle Pass to El Paso:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Reported regiment of Mexican troops will come through Texas tomorrow to
                            fight rebels in Chihuahua. Dangerous precedent, calculated inspire much
                            resentment against Texas in Mexico and may lead to grave eventualities.
                            You <pb facs="1007" n="891" xml:id="pg_891"/> should protest in name of
                            people of border against such action. Let Mexico handle troops on Mexico
                            soil. Texas not fighting Mexico’s battles. It is positively a disgrace
                            that Texas and American soil should be trodden by foreign soldiers
                            engaged in a civil war in neighboring country.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>If this is purpose of moving troops through Texas I withdraw my consent for them
                    to pass through Texas.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O. B. Colquitt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
